e portfolio due to this purchase was 0.16%. The holdings were 9,142 shares as of 2017-03-31.New Purchase: NxStage Medical Inc (NXTM)Athena Capital Advisors Llc initiated holdings in NxStage Medical Inc. The purchase prices were between $25.95 and $29.5, with an estimated average price of $27.62. The stock is now traded at around $27.13. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 0.1%. The holdings were 10,991 shares as of 2017-03-31.New Purchase: Johnson & Johnson (JNJ)Athena Capital Advisors Llc initiated holdings in Johnson & Johnson. The purchase prices were between $111.76 and $128.96, with an estimated average price of $119.46. The stock is now traded at around $123.33. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 0.09%. The holdings were 2,120 shares as of 2017-03-31.New Purchase: Automatic Data Processing Inc (ADP)Athena Capital Advisors Llc initiated holdings in Automatic Data Processing Inc. The purchase prices were between $95.25 and $105.11, with an estimated average price of $102. The stock is now traded at around $97.51. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 0.08%. The holdings were 2,380 shares as of 2017-03-31.Added: Berkshire Hathaway Inc (BRK.B)Athena Capital Advisors Llc added to the holdings in Berkshire Hathaway Inc by 55.08%. The purchase prices were between $158.81 and $177.28, with an estimated average price of $167.31. The stock is now traded at around $166.73. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 0.22%. The holdings were 10,908 shares as of 2017-03-31.Added: iShares MSCI EAFE (EFA)Athena Capital Advisors Llc added to the holdings in iShares MSCI EAFE by 77.85%. The purchase prices were between $57.73 and $62.6, with an estimated average price of $60.42. The stock is now traded at around $64.26. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 0.19%. The holdings were 21,198 shares as of 2017-03-31.Added: PepsiCo Inc (PEP)Athena Capital Advisors Llc added to the holdings in PepsiCo Inc by 56.60%. The purchase prices were between $101.55 and $112.45, with an estimated average price of $107.29. The stock is now traded at around $111.79. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 0.06%. The holdings were 4,150 shares as of 2017-03-31.Added: 3M Co (MMM)Athena Capital Advisors Llc added to the holdings in 3M Co by 74.84%. The purchase prices were between $174.18 and $193.01, with an estimated average price of $183.45. The stock is now traded at around $197.63. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 0.06%. The holdings were 2,126 shares as of 2017-03-31.Sold Out: Costco Wholesale Corp (COST)Athena Capital Advisors Llc sold out the holdings in Costco Wholesale Corp. The sale prices were between $159.73 and $177.98, with an estimated average price of $167.59.Sold Out: Dentsply Sirona Inc (XRAY)Athena Capital Advisors Llc sold out the holdings in Dentsply Sirona Inc. The sale prices were between $55.59 and $64.5, with an estimated average price of $60.19.Sold Out: Johnson Controls International PLC (JCI)Athena Capital Advisors Llc sold out the holdings in Johnson Controls International PLC. The sale prices were between $40.82 and $44.3, with an estimated average price of $42.28.Sold Out: Signet Jewelers Ltd (SIG)Athena Capital Advisors Llc sold out the holdings in Signet Jewelers Ltd. The sale prices were between $63.25 and $95.63, with an estimated average price of $74.77.Sold Out: Mohawk Industries Inc (MHK)Athena Capital Advisors Llc sold out the holdings in Mohawk Industries Inc. The sale prices were between $201.74 and $231.9, with an estimated average price of $219.75.Sold Out: Williams-Sonoma Inc (WSM)Athena Capital Advisors Llc sold out the holdings in Williams-Sonoma Inc. The sale prices were between $46.6 and $53.62, with an estimated average price of $48.73.BRK.B 15-Year Financial DataThe intrinsic value of BRK.BPeter Lynch Chart of BRK.BPremium MembersThis article first appeared on GuruFocus .



